In this project, I worked on predicting insurance costs based on personal and lifestyle factors like age, BMI, smoking habits, and region. I started by exploring the dataset to understand how these variables affect medical charges and looked for patterns and relationships between them. After cleaning and preparing the data, I applied different regression models and compared their performance to find the most accurate one. Through this project, I got a better understanding of how individual attributes influence insurance pricing and how predictive models can be used to estimate costs more effectively.
